    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as the clear engine of the offense. With an elite score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an optimal leadoff spot and a favorable matchup against S. Burke, whose 4.47 xERA provides a significant ceiling for production. Matching that intensity is **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), who leverages a juicy matchup against Michael McGreevy to climb the rankings; the synergy between his dynamic platoon advantage and a projected spot in the #2 hole makes him an essential start. **Jackson Merrill** (70.83) rounds out the high-upside group, as his matchup against M. Keller is buoyed by a 2% boost for stolen base potential\u2014critical for the Waves' roster construction given the premium placed on speed.\n\nWhile several players sit near the 50-point threshold, the decision to bench **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.94) was the most difficult. Despite his inherent talent and xwOBA profile, the matchup against an elite arm like Ohtani (2.67 xERA) suppresses his efficiency, rendering his projected output inferior to the platoon-advantaged **Josh Lowe** (62.99) and the consistent utility provided by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** We are also keeping a close eye on the volatility surrounding the back half of our lineup. **Luis Robert Jr.** carries a worrisome 48.72 score due to a significant platoon drag, and with multiple lineup spots still pending\u2014including **Liam Hicks**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe**\u2014our ultimate floor remains subject to change. If any of these pending spots drop further down the order, we may need to pivot to preserve our game caps.",
